# React Component Conventions

## Directory layout (apps)

```
src/
  app/           # routes.tsx, layouts/
  pages/         # route page components
  components/    # app-local components (incl. AsyncState helpers)
  config/        # site.ts, theme.ts
  lib/           # env.ts, api.ts (getApi bootstrap)
  content/       # static JSON/MDX
```

## Components

- Functional components; named exports for pages/layouts
- Shared primitives → `@ryx/ui`; app shells → `WebShell`, `H5Shell`
- Data fetching via `getApi()` from `@/lib/api` — no raw `fetch` in pages
- Every async page must handle loading, error, and empty states (see `error-handling.mdc`)

## Routing (react-router v7)

- Routes in `src/app/routes.tsx` via `createBrowserRouter`
- Lazy-load heavy pages with `React.lazy` + `Suspense` (see `performance.mdc`)

## Styling

- Tailwind utilities + `cn()` from `@ryx/ui/lib/utils`
- Design tokens in `packages/ui/src/styles/globals.css` (see `styling.mdc`)

## Page pattern

```tsx
import { getApi } from "@/lib/api";
import { AsyncContent } from "@/components/AsyncContent";

export function HomePage() {
  const { data, isLoading, error } = useProfile(); // hook wraps getApi()

  return (
    <AsyncContent isLoading={isLoading} error={error} isEmpty={!data}>
      {(profile) => <ProfileCard profile={profile} />}
    </AsyncContent>
  );
}
```
